#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""aq-wiki — Structured codebase wiki from knowledge-graph.json (OpenWiki pattern).

Reads .understand-anything/knowledge-graph.json → generates per-subsystem
markdown wiki sections in .understand-anything/wiki/<subsystem>.md.

Agents reference sections lazily (by path) instead of embedding raw files.
This mirrors OpenWiki's design: append references to instruction files,
let agents discover and fetch docs as needed.

Modes:
  aq-wiki --init          Full generation (all subsystems)
  aq-wiki --update        Differential: only subsystems with recent git changes
  aq-wiki --status        Wiki freshness and coverage table
  aq-wiki --list          List available sections with line counts
  aq-wiki --section NAME  Print named section to stdout
  aq-wiki --seed-aidb     Seed sections into AIDB wiki-sections collection

Usage by agents:
  cat .understand-anything/wiki/hybrid-coordinator.md  # direct read
  aq-wiki --section switchboard                        # CLI read
  aq-wiki --status                                     # freshness check before architecture work

Refresh cadence:
  After any code change:  aq-wiki --update  (adds to DOC-UPDATE step 7)
  After graph refresh:    aq-wiki --init --force
  In CI (if enabled):     aq-wiki --update && aq-wiki --seed-aidb
"""

